Package org.platanios.learn.combination.error

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ObjectiveFunction
    An interface specifying the methods that all classes defined as possible objective functions for the numerical optimization problem involved in the error rates estimation process should implement.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AgreementRatesPowerSetVector
    A structure that holds the agreement rates of all possible subsets of a set of functions of cardinality greater than or equal to 2.
    DataPreprocessing  
    DependencyObjectiveFunction
    An implementation of an objective function that quantifies the dependencies between the error rates of the different functions.
    ErrorRatesEstimation
    Handles the set up of the numerical optimization problem that needs to be solved in order to estimate error rates of several approximations to a single function, by using only the agreement rates of those functions on an unlabeled set of data.
    ErrorRatesEstimationTest  
    ErrorRatesPowerSetVector
    A structure that holds the individual error rates of a set of functions, as well as the joint error rates of all possible subsets of those functions.
    EstimationData
    A data structure that holds all the data necessary to estimate error rates of functions from unlabeled data.
    OptimizationProblem
    Implementation of the numerical optimization problem that needs to be solved in order to estimate error rates of several approximations to a single function, by using only the agreement rates of those functions on an unlabeled set of data, for use with the KNITRO solver.
    PowerSetVector
    A general implementation for storing elements indexed by a power set of integers (for example, indexed by: [0], [1], [2], [0,1], [0,2], [1,2] and [0,1,2]) as one-dimensional arrays and providing ways of accessing those elements.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ObjectiveFunctionType
    An enumeration of all possible objective function types that are currently supported by our implementation.
